snippet.textDisplay: I wish one day to try a street toast in Korea, but for now I have made it at home a couple of times. I like to add a slice of spam and a slice of cheese too! And I do put sugar on it now, but I also add some ground cardamom to the eggs. Gives them a nice bright gingery flavor.

And I do put sugar on it now, but I also add some ground cardamom to the eggs. Gives them a nice bright gingery flavor.

snippet.textDisplay: I love this recipe a whole lot! A tip for my fellow Aussies though - in Australia most households have tomato sauce as opposed to ketchup - tomato sauce is a lot sweeter than ketchup, so you can usually skip the sugar or reduce the amount you use as our sauce is much sweeter by default. <3 Definitely give this one a go, it's great!
